        </p>

        <ul>
          <li>
            <p>
 Understand how a two-dimensional system <m>\vec{x}' = P\vec{x}</m> 
      defines a vector field in the plane by assigning the vector 
      <m>P\vec{x}</m> to each point <m>\vec{x}</m>.
            </p>
          </li>

<li>
<p>
Identify <em>equilibrium points</em> as solutions of <m>P\vec{x} = \vec{0}</m> 
      and recognize that the origin is typically the unique equilibrium in a 
      homogeneous linear system.
</p>
</li>

          <li>
            <p>
 Describe how eigenvalues and eigenvectors of <m>P</m> determine basic 
      trajectory directions and qualitative motion in the <em>phase plane</em>.
            </p>
          </li>

        </ul>

</section>

